\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The prevailing capital-labour ratios for a given set of prices is the slope
 of the ray from the origin in the Edgeworth box
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
These rays from the origins are also called the Output Expansion Path
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
We saw this in our study of the Lerner diagram in lecture 2b
\end_layout

