Country PPF: North and South
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
For a given price, North is able to produce more computers, while South
 is able to produce more textile
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
In other words, for the price 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{C}/P_{T}$
\end_inset

 in the diagram, 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{T}/Q_{C}$
\end_inset

 is higher for South
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
This means that North's relative supply curve is to the left of South's
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Separator

\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
