\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Gains from Trade: South
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
In autarky, South had to produce its own computers
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
When countries are allowed to trade, prices converge and South goes from
 facing its autarky price 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(\frac{P_{T}}{P_{C}}\right)_{S}^{AUT}$
\end_inset

 to a higher global market price 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(\frac{P_{T}}{P_{C}}\right)^{TRADE}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Note in the PPF diagram, this is a decrease in 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{P_{C}}{P_{T}}$
\end_inset

---which is a flatter isovalue line
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
We see that following this change in relative price, South produces less
 computers and more textiles
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
By importing the extra computers they need and exporting their surplus of
 textiles, they achieve a higher indifference curve
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Separator

\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Gains from Trade: South
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

