\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
We have covered the three major results in the Heckscher-Ohlin Model
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Stolper-Samuelson Theorem
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Rybczynski Theorem
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Heckscher-Ohlin Theorem
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Together, they allowed us to answer
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
How changes in goods prices affect the return to factors
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
How changes in the stock of factors affect industrial composition
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
and how the stock of factors determine the goods countries will trade
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Next class
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Trade allow prices to converge, which causes factor prices to also converge
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
